            <h1>Nordic Sámi cooperation</h1>
            <div class="temaMobIngressImg" style="display: none;"><img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_nordisk150x113.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk
Author: Kenneth Hætta" /></div>
            <p class="textIngress">Sweden, Finland and Norway cooperate on Sámi issues, at both the civil service and
political levels.
</p>
            <img src="/upload/AID/temabilder/sami/tema_sami_nordisk150x113.jpg" alt="Samepolitikk
Author: Kenneth Hætta" class="temaIngressImg" />
            <div class="descriptionText"><p>Through the Nordic Government Officials Body for Sami Affairs, the authorities and the Sámi parliaments in the three countries meet regularly to exchange information and discuss. In 2001, regular cooperation was also established at the political level between the presidents of the Sámi parliaments and the ministers with responsibility for Sámi affairs in the three countries.<br /></p></div>
